This paper discusses a system for privilege separation and access control in IoT applications, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on high-level languages and their use in IoT applications, which suggests a possible fit with software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses access control techniques, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
